{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9028d966-d6fd-41bf-b0a3-a9ff7387509b","content":"With MTP (Microsoft.Testing.Platform), VSTest's `--filter` syntax is replaced by `--treenode-filter` which uses a path-based pattern with bracket notation for traits.\n\n**Old (VSTest / xUnit v2):**\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\n**New (MTP / xUnit v3):**\n```\ndotnet test --treenode-filter \"/**/*IntegrationTests*[Category=Smoke]\"\n```\n\nKey syntax differences:\n| VSTest | MTP tree-node filter |\n|--------|---------------------|\n| `FullyQualifiedName~X` (contains) | `/**/*X*` (glob pattern) |\n| `Category=Smoke` | `[Category=Smoke]` (bracket property) |\n| `&` (AND) | Combine path glob + `[trait]` inline |\n\nThe `/**/*IntegrationTests*` part matches any test whose fully-qualified name contains \"IntegrationTests\", and `[Category=Smoke]` filters to tests with that trait — same semantics as your original filter.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"2d970c49-0c49-47af-86b1-8a800b8fc938","outputTokens":275,"requestId":"6809:10DA83:77B040:7F2CBE:6A044DD5"},"id":"0543a48e-3fd6-4e55-be87-71ab547743e1","timestamp":"2026-05-13T10:09:34.814Z","parentId":"498bbc44-2cd4-423b-9fb2-bad28417bb3c"}
